SIMPLE: pneumogastric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pneumogastric
<hw>Pneu`mo*gas"tric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pneumo-</ets> + <ets>gastric</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the lungs and the stomach.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The pneumogastric nerve.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pneumogastric nerve</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>one
of the tenth pair of cranial nerves which are distributed to the
pharynx, esophagus, larynx, lungs, heart, stomach, liver, and spleen,
and, in fishes and many amphibia, to the branchial apparatus and also to
the sides of the body.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pneumograph</ent>⟦br⟧
